snippet.textDisplay: I am blown away by this song. I am gujarati and I am proud of this work. But still have questions - why use 'kharvo' as an adjective to 'khalasi' when both mean the same? And why 'tham ne thekana' when it means the same? We say 'nam ne thekana' when we donot know a person but know there shd be someone like that or have heard stories about someone' Also English script of Gujarati word is coming as 'Gotilo', it should be 'Goti lo' - i understand it is autogenerated but can be fixed
snippet.textOriginal: I am blown away by this song. I am gujarati and I am proud of this work. But still have questions - why use 'kharvo' as an adjective to 'khalasi' when both mean the same? And why 'tham ne thekana' when it means the same? We say 'nam ne thekana' when we donot know a person but know there shd be someone like that or have heard stories about someone' Also English script of Gujarati word is coming as 'Gotilo', it should be 'Goti lo' - i understand it is autogenerated but can be fixed
